ltshire, England":"Wilton, Wiltshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Eland","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Elland (Yorkshire) or Little Eland (Northumberland), both of which derive their names from Old English <i>ēaland</i> ‘cultivated land by water or a river’.","Dutch: from a personal name composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>adel</i> ‘noble’ + <i>land</i> ‘land’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Wymarka","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Norman, English: relationship name from the Old Breton personal name  <i>Wiuhomarch</i>.  See also  Wymer   (2)."],"variants":[{"name":"Whymark","meanings":["Norman, English:  see  Wymark  ."]},{"name":"Wymer","meanings":["English (Norfolk): from the Middle English personal name <i>Wymer</i>, Old English <i>Wīgmǣr</i> (composed of the elements <i>wīg</i> ‘war’ + <i>mǣr</i> ‘famous’), reinforced by the cognate ancient Germanic form <i>Wigmar</i>, introduced into England from France by the Normans. Compare   Wimmer   5. Among the Normans, this name became confused with an Old Breton personal name, <i>Wiumarch</i>, composed of the elements <i>uuiu</i> ‘worthy’ + <i>march</i> ‘horse’.","Altered form of German   Weimer  ."]},{"name":"Waymark","meanings":["Norman, English:  see  Wymark  ."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of any of the given names beginning with the letter <i>D-</i> (  compare  Jay   and   Kay  ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":49,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":58,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":93,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Wymarka de Eland was born about 1166, in Elland, Yorkshire, England, her father, Hugh de Eland, was 57 and her mother, Mrs. Hugh de Eland, was 52. She had at least 2 sons with Jordan de Mitton. She died in Wilton, Wiltshire, England."},"et":{"about 1166–":"umbes 1166–Surnud","1166–Female":"1166–Surnud","–1195":"–1195","–Male":"Surnud","1210–Male":"1210–Surnud","1110–1166":"1110–1166","1115–Female":"1115–Surnud","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1115":"1115","1224":"1224","1133":"1133","1210":"1210","1166":"1166","1110":"1110","1195":"1195","about 1166":"umbes 1166","about 1210":"1210","Clitheroe, Lancashire, England":"Clitheroe, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Elland, Yorkshire, England":"Elland, Yorkshire, England","Wilton, Wiltshire, England":"Wilton, Wiltshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1166–":"noin 1166–Kuollut","1166–Female":"1166–Kuollut","–1195":"–1195","–Male":"Kuollut","1210–Male":"1210–Kuollut","1110–11